snippet.textDisplay:
I'm surprised the Borstel Ballista wasn't listed. 

I've been shredding everything with it. Even at level 41, I beat the final boss at level 49 with it relatively easily and could still one shot tons of lvl 49 enemies too. 

Luckily got it from a vendor at lvl 50 now, and still loving it. Get an ammo regen skill/mod and you are set.

Note: I've been hopping between home/silo bases right before calling it a night and typically find anywhere between 1-4 legendary items across each run. That's how I got the lvl 41 Borstel Ballista. 
Not sure it was supposed to be a vendor item or not, but I'm not complaining.

snippet.textDisplay:
Man the Wombo Combo is no joke. I have a level 27 Radiation Wombo Combo that I used up until I hit about level 45. It was STILL better than most of the other loot that dropped for me. Even other higher lvl legendaries.

Also just to add about the phantom flame. Yes it IS an overwatch reference. But remember The Presequel came out in 2014, 2 years before Overwatch. And Nisha's skill was Showdown, which was basically a combination of Mcree and Soldiers ultimates in Overwatch 2 years later. Soooo you could argue they're just reimplementing Showdown in that legendary perk, whilst also nodding to Overwatch.
